    "## Part 3: Murmurations\n",
    "\n",
    "Discovered by Pozdnyakov (2022): when averaging $a_p/\\sqrt{p}$\n",
    "over many curves of the same rank, **coherent waves emerge**\n",
    "oscillating in opposite directions for different ranks.\n",
    "\n",
    "Named after starling murmurations — individually chaotic, collectively structured.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Key observations (identifiable visually):**\n",
    "- Points follow the **Sato-Tate distribution** (semicircle, bounded ±2)\n",
    "- They gravitate toward zero — **Hasse's theorem** (1930)\n",
    "- The average drifts in **opposite directions** per rank"
   ]
